# OpenSpec + idea log

1. Read [openspec/AGENTS.md](openspec/AGENTS.md) for folder layout, proposal template, and validation checklist.
2. Read [openspec/project.md](openspec/project.md) for domain vocabulary.
3. For **secrets and review norms**, read [openspec/specs/repo-privacy/spec.md](openspec/specs/repo-privacy/spec.md) and [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md). For **past mistakes and guards**, read [LEARNINGS.md](LEARNINGS.md) and [openspec/specs/operational-learning/spec.md](openspec/specs/operational-learning/spec.md).
4. Do not edit [openspec/specs](openspec/specs) without a corresponding `openspec/changes/<slug>/` (see **Forbidden** in [openspec/AGENTS.md](openspec/AGENTS.md)).
5. Before apply: `npm run spec:validate` must pass.
6. For `ideas/log.ndjson` and capture schema, follow [openspec/specs/idea-capture/spec.md](openspec/specs/idea-capture/spec.md) and [.claude/commands/kiruk-capture.md](.claude/commands/kiruk-capture.md) when logging sessions.
